						<div class="postbody">I take nocash to be highlighting how there are two components to this: a window of time when rendering enabled/disabled is observed by the PPU, and then a point where it skips a pixel, which could be much later. I beleive the tests don't pin down when it's skipped, just that it occurs sometime that frame. I wonder whether I ever wrote some that do the toggle and then something timing-dependent like sprite #0 hit in the first line to be sure the effect on timing had taken place.</div>

