						<div class="postbody">On a NTSC SNES it works so:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; At Line 0:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;field=field XOR 1&nbsp; ;toggle even/odd frame<br />&nbsp; At Line 240:&nbsp; &nbsp;IF field=1 THEN skip last dot of Line 240<br /></div><br />On NES it might be same or similar. If it is so, then I would interprete the existing test/info as so:<br />The &quot;toggle&quot; takes place in Line 261 (according to the wiki page) (or maybe it's actually Line 0 as on SNES).<br />The &quot;skip&quot; location is unknown (except, it CANNOT occur within the visible 224 lines, since then even totally blind people would have noticed the curvy lines effect in mid-screen).</div>

