					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm not keen enough on the electrical-engineering type knowledge on it, but I can tell you that the skewed-line effect on a CRT TV is affected by the contrast between the vertical line and the surrounding data around it, and is a product of the CRT TV's physical method of shooting the beam at the phosphors. A capture card would not show it, and a CRT TV that is high-end and/or in extremely good condition would not show it either.</div>

