						<div class="postbody">I just tried this and I think the skipped dot is just before the first scanline as you doubted. My video capture shows every other field with some bending to the left of a clean left edge, with the first line shifted left about a pixel, the next about 2/3, the next maybe 1/4, and then it's back in line. When I have a program enable rendering late (about 2386 cycles from VBL), the frame has a clean left edge on every field, right up to the top. I think my video capture might not get the very top active scanline, so it might be shifted even more to the left were it shown.<br /><br />I had always thought this slight distortion was just unavoidable. Interesting that it's due to a deficiency in the PPU video signal.</div>

