					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I pinned down where the dot skip occurs in Visual 2C02 earlier - see the diagram and notes section in <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/images/d/d1/Ntsc_timing.png">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/images/d/d1/Ntsc_timing.png</a><!-- m -->. I think I also confirmed that the skip only occurs if the PPU is enabled at the end of the pre-render line (i.e., enabling the PPU right before the end of the line causes the skip to occur, but not right after).<br /><br />There's a short &quot;user's manual&quot; for Visual 2C02 at <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Visual_2C02">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Visual_2C02</a><!-- m --> now btw in case you want to confirm stuff for yourselves. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />Edit: I just realized the notes section has contradictory information on where the first pixel is output. I'll get on that...</div>

